      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:1:3:2:5",
      "text": [
        " إِنَّ اللَّهَ خِلْوٌ مِنْ خَلْقِهِ وَ خَلْقَهُ خِلْوٌ مِنْهُ وَ كُلُّ مَا وَقَعَ عَلَيْهِ اسْمُ شَيْ‏ءٍ مَا خَلَا اللَّهَ تَعَالَى فَهُوَ مَخْلُوقٌ وَ اللَّهُ خَالِقُ كُلِّ شَيْ‏ءٍ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Ali Bin Ibrahim, from his father, from Ibn Abu Umeyr, from Ali Bin Atiyya, from Khaysama, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Ja’far<sup>asws</sup> having said: ‘Allah<sup>azwj</sup> is Distinct from His<sup>azwj</sup> creation and His<sup>azwj</sup> creation is distinct from Him<sup>azwj</sup>, and everything what the name ‘thing’ occurs upon, apart from Allah<sup>azwj</sup> the Exalted, so it is a creation, and Allah<sup>azwj</sup> is the Creator of everything’."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          " 5. It is narrated from Imam abu Ja‘far (a.s.) who said, “ Allah is distinct from His creatures and the creatures are different from Him and whatever could be called a thing is a creature except Allah Who is the Creator of all things.”"
        ]
      }
    },
